But in the absence of
commitment devices,

00:12:54.100 --> 00:12:56.080
people may still make
suboptimal decisions.

00:12:56.080 --> 00:12:58.660
And some of these
decisions might, in fact,

00:12:58.660 --> 00:13:00.490
induce large welfare needs.

00:13:00.490 --> 00:13:02.970
We discussed some
examples in class,

00:13:02.970 --> 00:13:04.640
sort of numerical
examples, where

00:13:04.640 --> 00:13:07.450
you could see that sophisticated
people might actually

00:13:07.450 --> 00:13:11.170
be worse off than naive
people, and could in fact

00:13:11.170 --> 00:13:14.210
suffer quite a bit from or
similar to the large welfare

00:13:14.210 --> 00:13:14.710
losses.

00:13:14.710 --> 00:13:16.600
With the present
bias, all of this

00:13:16.600 --> 00:13:19.360
is evaluated by the
long-run [INAUDIBLE] ideas

00:13:19.360 --> 00:13:24.730
of like if somebody makes
choices for the future where

00:13:24.730 --> 00:13:27.770
the beta is not
relevant, compared

00:13:27.770 --> 00:13:30.150
to that kind of
welfare criterion,

00:13:30.150 --> 00:13:34.650
people might be a lot worse
off due to their present bias.

00:13:34.650 --> 00:13:36.820
OK, here's example number three.

00:13:36.820 --> 00:13:39.640
Present bias individuals
always have positive demand

00:13:39.640 --> 00:13:42.320
for commitment devices.

00:13:42.320 --> 00:13:45.960
Again, the statement is false.

00:13:45.960 --> 00:13:46.550
Why is that?

00:13:46.550 --> 00:13:48.200
And we kind of
discussed this already

00:13:48.200 --> 00:13:50.055
in the previous questions.

00:13:50.055 --> 00:13:51.425
Now, let me be very explicit.

00:13:51.425 --> 00:13:53.180
There's sort of
three conditions that

00:13:53.180 --> 00:13:55.470
must be met for positive
demand for commitment.

00:13:55.470 --> 00:13:57.610
I discussed this in class.

00:13:57.610 --> 00:13:59.570
We know that person
must be present biased,

00:13:59.570 --> 00:14:02.533
or have some form of some
self-control problems.

00:14:02.533 --> 00:14:03.950
Individuals must--
the person must

00:14:03.950 --> 00:14:07.170
be aware of the present bias,
so they can't be fully naive.

00:14:07.170 --> 00:14:10.370
They could be partially naive,
but it can't be fully naive.

00:14:10.370 --> 00:14:12.725
And the individual must
perceive the commitment device

00:14:12.725 --> 00:14:16.293
as effective in helping overcome
the self-control problem.

00:14:16.293 --> 00:14:18.710
That's to say, if somebody is
offered a commitment device,

00:14:18.710 --> 00:14:20.660
and that commitment
device is useless,

00:14:20.660 --> 00:14:23.570
well, there's not going to
be any demand for commitment,

00:14:23.570 --> 00:14:26.240
particularly if the person
perceives that the commitment

00:14:26.240 --> 00:14:28.887
device is useless.

00:14:28.887 --> 00:14:30.470
Notice that that
person might actually

00:14:30.470 --> 00:14:32.590
perceive the commitment
device to be effective,

00:14:32.590 --> 00:14:33.938
while in reality, it's not.

00:14:33.938 --> 00:14:36.230
So they might have some
positive demand for commitment,

00:14:36.230 --> 00:14:38.930
even if the commitment
device is in reality useless,

00:14:38.930 --> 00:14:41.360
because their beliefs are
wrong, because of essentially

00:14:41.360 --> 00:14:44.690
some form of partial naivete.

00:14:44.690 --> 00:14:47.570
But it cannot be that the person
perceives the commitment device

00:14:47.570 --> 00:14:50.120
as not effective, because
then the person would just not

00:14:50.120 --> 00:14:52.110
demand it in the first place.

00:14:52.110 --> 00:14:54.920
Now, that makes now
the statement false.

00:14:54.920 --> 00:14:57.170
When only the first condition
of the three is met,

00:14:57.170 --> 00:15:00.050
as in like the person's
only present-biased,

00:15:00.050 --> 00:15:03.500
then we cannot be sure that
there will be positive demand

00:15:03.500 --> 00:15:06.740
for commitment.

00:15:06.740 --> 00:15:09.860
And so the statement,
as had been said,

00:15:09.860 --> 00:15:13.040
is false, because we said
sort of like always have

00:15:13.040 --> 00:15:14.840
positive demand for commitment.

00:15:14.840 --> 00:15:16.990
If it were without
the always, then

00:15:16.990 --> 00:15:19.590
you could also answer uncertain,
because then you would say,

00:15:19.590 --> 00:15:22.160
well, it depends
on their naivete,

00:15:22.160 --> 00:15:26.390
or on the sophistication, or
it depends on how effective

00:15:26.390 --> 00:15:27.830
the commitment device is.

00:15:27.830 --> 00:15:30.830
But the way the statement is
written, it says like, always.

00:15:30.830 --> 00:15:32.360
And so now, you
can easily come up

00:15:32.360 --> 00:15:36.170
with some counterexamples that
show that the statement in fact

00:15:36.170 --> 00:15:36.850
is false.

