00:28:32.700 --> 00:28:35.910
OK, so then here's
another example

00:28:35.910 --> 00:28:37.800
of a true/false/uncertain
question.

00:28:37.800 --> 00:28:40.570
Statement, if a person
gives 0 in a dictator game,

00:28:40.570 --> 00:28:44.430
this is evidence that
this person is selfish.

00:28:44.430 --> 00:28:46.860
Now, the answer is false.

00:28:46.860 --> 00:28:48.490
I think if you
answer it uncertain,

00:28:48.490 --> 00:28:50.310
that would also be fine.

00:28:50.310 --> 00:28:51.060
Why is that?

00:28:51.060 --> 00:28:55.230
Well, the person might
give 0 to the other person

00:28:55.230 --> 00:28:58.745
in the dictator game and then
donate the money to someone

00:28:58.745 --> 00:28:59.807
in greater need, right?

00:28:59.807 --> 00:29:01.890
And then that person is
in fact really quite nice.

00:29:04.590 --> 00:29:06.242
Second, the person
might be very poor

00:29:06.242 --> 00:29:07.950
relative to the other
person in the game.

00:29:07.950 --> 00:29:10.650
So her marginal utility
is just very high.

00:29:10.650 --> 00:29:13.200
So now, even if you
have like equal weights

00:29:13.200 --> 00:29:17.460
to your own utility and
the other person's utility,

00:29:17.460 --> 00:29:21.090
since the marginal utility of
giving $10 to yourself compared

00:29:21.090 --> 00:29:23.820
to the other person is way
higher than the other person's

00:29:23.820 --> 00:29:28.687
marginal utility, you would just
give everything to yourself.

00:29:28.687 --> 00:29:30.770
And that doesn't mean you
don't care about others.

00:29:30.770 --> 00:29:33.380
It just means
like, in fact, even

00:29:33.380 --> 00:29:36.655
if you were sort of
like a social climber,

00:29:36.655 --> 00:29:38.030
you would give it
to that person,

00:29:38.030 --> 00:29:39.780
because that person
was like a huge meany,

00:29:39.780 --> 00:29:42.682
or the rich person just might
not really need that money.

00:29:42.682 --> 00:29:44.390
Looking at this more
closely, actually, I

00:29:44.390 --> 00:29:47.310
think uncertain would be a
better answer here, and not

00:29:47.310 --> 00:29:47.810
false.

00:29:47.810 --> 00:29:50.790
I just wrote this
question fairly quickly.

00:29:50.790 --> 00:29:53.430
So if the question says--

00:29:53.430 --> 00:29:55.020
if the question
instead were to say,

00:29:55.020 --> 00:29:59.030
this is conclusive evidence
that this person is selfish,

00:29:59.030 --> 00:30:01.340
then it would be false.

00:30:01.340 --> 00:30:03.200
Or this would be,
this is clearly

00:30:03.200 --> 00:30:04.760
evidence where
this person must be

00:30:04.760 --> 00:30:07.880
selfish, that would be false.

00:30:07.880 --> 00:30:10.670
The way it's written right now,
it's rather sort of uncertain,

00:30:10.670 --> 00:30:12.180
because we just
don't quite know.

00:30:12.180 --> 00:30:16.520
It could be that the
person is really selfish.

00:30:16.520 --> 00:30:19.320
Or it could be that the person--

00:30:19.320 --> 00:30:21.770
it could be this evidence
that the person is selfish.

00:30:21.770 --> 00:30:26.680
But it could be the other two
reasons that I just mentioned.

00:30:26.680 --> 00:30:30.640
OK, so now, finally, I'm going
