00:30:49.020 --> 00:30:52.310
So assume the 14.13
students are present

00:30:52.310 --> 00:30:57.020
biased with beta small
than 1 and delta equals 0.

00:30:57.020 --> 00:30:59.450
All students have
the same beta smaller

00:30:59.450 --> 00:31:01.160
than 1 and delta equals 0.

00:31:01.160 --> 00:31:04.580
But they differ in
the value they derive

00:31:04.580 --> 00:31:07.680
from using laptops in class.

00:31:07.680 --> 00:31:11.050
L is constant for each
student from class to class,

00:31:11.050 --> 00:31:14.790
but uniformly distributed
across students on the interval

00:31:14.790 --> 00:31:17.260
between 0 and 1.

00:31:17.260 --> 00:31:21.460
So some people have
like a huge value

00:31:21.460 --> 00:31:25.255
of using the laptop in class.

00:31:25.255 --> 00:31:29.400
And others do not.

00:31:29.400 --> 00:31:32.100
Each lecture generates
no immediate utility.

00:31:32.100 --> 00:31:35.160
So it's neither fun nor
like annoying or the like.

00:31:35.160 --> 00:31:40.730
But it does give a benefit,
a future benefit of V.

00:31:40.730 --> 00:31:42.260
So like you might
learn something,

00:31:42.260 --> 00:31:45.110
or there's some things that
might be valuable to you

00:31:45.110 --> 00:31:46.280
in the future.

00:31:46.280 --> 00:31:50.810
Using a laptop reduces
the long-run benefit by D.

00:31:50.810 --> 00:31:53.730
This might be like
distractions, in particular.

00:31:53.730 --> 00:31:56.570
So you might be
distracted during class

00:31:56.570 --> 00:31:57.860
when you use a laptop.

00:31:57.860 --> 00:32:01.320
So the future benefits
are diminished by that.

00:32:01.320 --> 00:32:03.410
Maybe he had said something
really insightful,

00:32:03.410 --> 00:32:07.400
you didn't pay attention,
and so now, the benefits

00:32:07.400 --> 00:32:11.540
is B minus D if
you use a laptop.

00:32:11.540 --> 00:32:14.340
Both B and D are the
same for all students.

00:32:14.340 --> 00:32:18.170
So there's no variation
across students there.

00:32:18.170 --> 00:32:21.120
The only variation's coming
from some students who really,

00:32:21.120 --> 00:32:24.080
really like using laptops
for various reasons, perhaps

00:32:24.080 --> 00:32:27.560
because they like to
surf the internet.

00:32:27.560 --> 00:32:31.940
Perhaps they're really
in need of using laptops

00:32:31.940 --> 00:32:35.740
because that allows them
to take proper notes.

00:32:35.740 --> 00:32:40.470
So in summary, a student
uses a laptop in class--

00:32:40.470 --> 00:32:42.810
sorry, a student that
uses the laptop in class

00:32:42.810 --> 00:32:46.590
gets immediate utility L and
future, undiscounted utility

00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:50.340
of B minus D. And a student
who does not use a laptop

00:32:50.340 --> 00:32:55.390
gets immediate utility of 0 and
future discounted utility of V.

00:32:55.390 --> 00:32:59.320
So and now the social
planner is not present biased

00:32:59.320 --> 00:33:03.100
and seeks to maximize the
utility of 14.13 students

00:33:03.100 --> 00:33:05.298
from his perspective, OK?

00:33:08.620 --> 00:33:10.680
First question.

00:33:10.680 --> 00:33:14.340
Show that students are just
indifferent between using

00:33:14.340 --> 00:33:18.300
and not using a laptop
in the current class

00:33:18.300 --> 00:33:21.960
if L equals beat
times D. Explain

00:33:21.960 --> 00:33:24.270
why students with
lower values of L--

00:33:24.270 --> 00:33:27.150
so that's like L being
lower than beta D--

00:33:27.150 --> 00:33:29.070
don't use laptops in
class, but students

00:33:29.070 --> 00:33:30.570
with higher values of L--

00:33:30.570 --> 00:33:32.290
so L exceeds beta D--

00:33:32.290 --> 00:33:35.450
do use laptops in class.

00:33:35.450 --> 00:33:37.310
OK, so now what
we're going to do

00:33:37.310 --> 00:33:40.280
is we're going to write down the
utilities from the two choices.

00:33:40.280 --> 00:33:44.660
That's essentially already
given in the explanation,

00:33:44.660 --> 00:33:48.170
except for that we need to be
careful of where the beta comes

00:33:48.170 --> 00:33:48.750
in, right?

00:33:48.750 --> 00:33:52.130
So if students use
a laptop in class,

00:33:52.130 --> 00:33:55.220
they get the immediate benefit
of L. And then in the future,

00:33:55.220 --> 00:33:58.360
they get what's discounted by
beta, which is beta times B

00:33:58.360 --> 00:34:01.867
minus D, right, because
both B and D are very far

00:34:01.867 --> 00:34:02.450
in the future.

00:34:02.450 --> 00:34:06.620
These are the benefits, or the
diminished benefits, B minus D,

00:34:06.620 --> 00:34:08.210
that they get in the future.

00:34:08.210 --> 00:34:11.670
L is in the present, so
there's no beta here.

00:34:11.670 --> 00:34:14.820
Instead, if someone uses no
laptop, the students get 0.

00:34:14.820 --> 00:34:17.760
So there's no laptop
benefits in the present.

00:34:17.760 --> 00:34:21.690
And the benefits in
the future, the value

00:34:21.690 --> 00:34:24.360
of the lecture the
future is undiminished,

00:34:24.360 --> 00:34:26.429
which means essentially,
it's just V.

00:34:26.429 --> 00:34:32.570
So the person just gets
0 plus beta times V.

00:34:32.570 --> 00:34:37.219
Now, students who are
indifferent, by definition,

00:34:37.219 --> 00:34:40.670
have the same utility of using
laptops and using no laptop.

00:34:40.670 --> 00:34:44.929
So we can essentially just
equate those two things.

00:34:44.929 --> 00:34:48.020
Notice that like the beta
times B is always there.

00:34:48.020 --> 00:34:50.239
So it sort of
essentially just cancels.

00:34:50.239 --> 00:34:53.389
And then what we get is the
person that's indifferent,

00:34:53.389 --> 00:34:57.990
for that person, L
equals beta times D.

00:34:57.990 --> 00:35:02.010
Now, students that
choose not to use laptops

00:35:02.010 --> 00:35:05.490
will have low valuations
L of using laptops,

00:35:05.490 --> 00:35:07.980
while students that
choose to use the laptops

00:35:07.980 --> 00:35:10.215
have high L, right?

00:35:10.215 --> 00:35:13.110
If L is very large, then
it exceeds beta times D.

00:35:13.110 --> 00:35:17.010
If L is very small,
then L does not exceed,

00:35:17.010 --> 00:35:18.660
is smaller than beta times D.

00:35:18.660 --> 00:35:21.090
So given the
indifference condition,

00:35:21.090 --> 00:35:24.780
we have essentially, as I just
said, students that do not

00:35:24.780 --> 00:35:28.720
use the laptop, L is smaller
than beta times D. And students

00:35:28.720 --> 00:35:35.570
that use the laptop, for them,
L is larger than beta times D.

00:35:35.570 --> 00:35:37.000
OK.

00:35:37.000 --> 00:35:39.700
OK, now question number two.

